summaries.short: After struggling to make romantic connections throughout her adolescence and college days, Darby finally falls in (requited) love.
summaries.full: Following her parents’ divorce, Darby Carter struggled to make connections as an adolescent and, later, as a NYU student, until she meets Augie Jeong at a karaoke party. After their whirlwind night together and several days spent waiting by the phone for Augie’s follow-up “WYD” text, Darby quickly finds herself in a comfortable, full-blown relationship.

summaries.short: A year after Augie, Darby falls for her recently divorced boss, Bradley.
summaries.full: A year later, Darby’s life and career feel stagnant. When sparks fly with Bradley, her former boss who’s recently divorced and highly successful, Darby feels pressure to revisit her half-baked dream of becoming a photographer, but soon gets swept up into girlfriend duties instead.

summaries.short: Darby runs into an old flame and spends the rest of the day trying to get him off her mind.
summaries.full: After Darby runs into an old flame and his new girlfriend, her best friend Sara, who’s eager to bail on her long-term boyfriend Jim’s family obligation, convinces Darby to join her at a coworker’s rooftop party. After hours spent stalking her ex’s new girl on social media, she winds up connecting with an overeager, romantically bruised Danny.
